EmailTemplate.Body:
Hello,
An IdentityIQ administrator has asked you to approve linking an uncorrelated account to one of your direct reports. Nothing is changed until you approve.
================================================== ACCOUNT TO BE LINKED ================================================== Orphan account : ${orcNativeIdentity} Application : ${orcApplicationName}
================================================== SUGGESTED IDENTITY ================================================== Name : ${orcIdentityDisplay} Login : ${orcIdentityName}
================================================== MATCH CONFIDENCE ================================================== Score : ${orcScore} / 100 Reason : ${orcMatchDetail}
-------------------------------------------------- WHAT TO DO -------------------------------------------------- 1. Log in to IdentityIQ. 2. Go to My Work > Approvals. 3. Open this request. The full account details (status, last login and sample access) are shown on the work item. 4. Approve to link the account to ${orcIdentityDisplay}, or Reject if it does not belong to them.
The account is linked ONLY after you approve. If you reject, nothing changes.
This is an automated message from the Orphan Account Correlator.

Hello ${adminDisplayName},

A manager has responded to your orphan account correlation approval request.

--- Summary ---
Account:          ${nativeIdentity}
Matched Identity: ${identityDisplayName}
Match Score:      ${score}/100
Decision:         ${decision}
Manager Comment:  ${comments}

--- Outcome ---
${outcome}

If the decision was REJECTED, the account remains uncorrelated and you
may wish to investigate further.

This is an automated notification from the Orphan Account Correlator.
